Internally displaced persons in Nyanza have threatened to demonstrate next week if their Sh3 billion compensation is not released.Their chairman Nelson Owegi questioned why the money has not been sent to them, yet it has been released by the Treasury.He said on November 5, they were told the money would be sent in two weeks.&ldquo;We are asking Adan Wachu [National Consultative Coordination Committee on IDPs chairman] where our money is and why they are not releasing it. We are sure the money is currently at the National Consultative Committee secretariat," Owegi said.